      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "NOSIE BY NATURE (4) got home strongly last start to finish a close second at headquarters when resuming. Is sure to have come on from that and looks the one to beat. TRIPOD TERROR (3) rattled home late to finish a close third last start over this track and trip to make it four minor placings in a row. Well placed this and there's no reason he can't find winning ways. TOUR DE MOON (2) was a determined maiden winner last time out, scoring by a long neck over this course and distance. Sparingly raced and has more to offer. Looks well placed and he is one of the main chances. ZOUTRAIL (8) is third-up and looks close to a win after finishing a close second last time out at Balaklava. Worth including on her latest effort.",
